title: Millburn High School junior varsity boys cross country team wins title
text:
Millburn High School junior varsity boys cross country team wins title October 8, 2015 Last updated: Thursday, October 8, 2015, 12:32 AM The Item of Millburn and Short Hills Print 
Millburn junior varsity boys squad extends title run 
Noah Yadgaroff, Danny Sullivan and Dean Portugal logged a 1-2-3 finish Oct. 6, powering Millburn High School’s junior varsity boys cross country team to a fifth consecutive Super Essex Conference championship race crown at Branch Brook Park in Newark. 
Yadgaroff, a junior, paced the 257-runner field in 17:57.8. 
Sullivan, a senior, crossed the finish line in 18:01.1 Portugal, a senior, finished in 18:16.0. 
Seniors Justin Blackman (eighth, 18:49.9) and Billy Muller (10th, 18:59.0) also contributed to Millburn’s team score. 
Millburn claimed the team title with 24 points. 
Seton Hall Preparatory School placed second with 53 points. 
Montclair High School (76 points) came in third followed by Columbia High School (105 points) and Bloomfield High School (181 points). 
Visit www.essexcountytrack.bizland.com to view complete race results.
